# Component Structure

- Each component must be in its own folder named after the component.
- The component entry file must be `index.tsx`.
- Keep styles in a `styles.module.css` file.
- Keep constants in a `consts` file.
- Keep helpers in a `utils` file.
- Keep component types in a `types` file.
- Declare components as named exports using arrow functions.
- Type component props explicitly (no implicit `any` props).

## Component Declaration Style

```tsx
import type { ButtonProps } from './types';

export const Button = (props: ButtonProps) => {
  return <button>{props.children}</button>;
};
```

## Expected Example

```text
MyComponent/
  index.tsx
  styles.module.css
  consts.ts
  utils.ts
  types.ts
```
